oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Chickasaw Mills
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of Chickasaw Mills. There are people on the porch and in the yard. Maria Blanton Currier, wife of Nathaniel Currier, is standing on the porch.
Chickasaw Mills was built in 1833 by J. Currier.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
